Reasoning: The paper discusses the process of building a mental model of surroundings and using it to extrapolate to new unseen locations, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning techniques to learn features rather than a map suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper may also involve natural language processing (cs.CL) if it discusses the use of language to describe and navigate environments.
